A voice-over talent and speech coach, Seun Shobo, has become the first African to be elected to the Board of Directors of the international professional body,Â  Voice and Speech Trainers Association. VASTA, which has its headquarters in Washington, United States of America, is an international organisation of over 5000 members whose mission is to advance the research and visibility of the voice and speech profession globally. Shobo, who is the founder of Voice Over Academy and VoiceOverBank, described the appointment by VATSA as laudable, stating that Nigeria and Africa are gradually being recognised as reference points for excellence on the international stage. He also stated that opportunities abound for African talents with the latest recognition for the continent by the global body that has existed for over three decades. He is expected to be the African representative on the VASTA board for a three-year term. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com